TITLE: Reference Script Tier Price Calculation
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how the referenceScriptTierPrice is calculated based on the size of reference scripts.  It defines a tier-based pricing model where the cost per byte increases as the size of the reference scripts grows. Understanding this pricing model is critical for optimizing transactions with reference scripts to minimize fees.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emurgo/ogmios/blob/master/docs/content/changelog/_index.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: LaTeX
CODE:
```
referenceScriptTierPrice_{80KiB} = 25600 \times (44 + 52.8 + 63.36) + 5120 \times 76.032 = 4489379
```

