TITLE: Ogmios WebSocket Interaction
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to interact with Ogmios using the WebSocket protocol.  It uses the `ws` Node.js package to establish a connection, send a `findIntersection` request, and process the response. It requires the `ws` package to be installed (`npm install ws`).
SOURCE: https://github.com/emurgo/ogmios/blob/master/docs/content/getting-started/basics.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const WebSocket = require('ws');
const client = new WebSocket("ws://localhost:1337");

client.once('open', () => {
    const request = {
        "jsonrpc": "2.0",
        "method": "findIntersection",
        "params": { "points": [ "origin" ] }
    };
    client.send(JSON.stringify(request));
});

client.on('message', function(msg) {
  const response = JSON.parse(msg);

  // do something with 'response'
});
```

