TITLE: Pipelining `nextBlock` requests with JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code demonstrates how to pipeline `nextBlock` requests to Ogmios using a WebSocket connection. It bursts the server's queue with multiple requests initially and then sends a new request immediately after receiving each response, optimizing bandwidth utilization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emurgo/ogmios/blob/master/docs/content/mini-protocols/local-chain-sync.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const nextBlock = JSON.stringify({
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "nextBlock",
});

client.on('open', () => {
  // Burst the server's queue with a few requests.
  for (let i = 0; i < 100; i += 1) {
    client.send(nextBlock);
  }
});

client.on('message', msg => {
  client.send(nextBlock); // Ask for next request immediately
  doSomething(msg);
})
```

