TITLE: Execution Units Evaluator Handle Interface - Haskell
DESCRIPTION: This Haskell data type defines an interface for evaluating execution units. It includes a function `evaluateExecutionUnitsM` that takes a UTxO set and a serialized transaction as input, and returns an `EvaluateTxResponse` within a monadic context `m`. This allows for decoupling the evaluation process from the tx-submission client.
