TITLE: Main Function with Logging Setup in Haskell
DESCRIPTION: The main function sets up the logging environment using `withStdoutTracer` and runs the HTTP and DB applications concurrently, passing the respective tracers to them. It depends on functions like `myHttpApplication` and `myDbApplication` to function correctly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emurgo/ogmios/blob/master/server/modules/contra-tracers/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: haskell
CODE:
```
main :: IO ()
main = do
    withStdoutTracer mempty emptyConfiguration $ \tracers -> do
        concurrently_
            (myHttpApplication (tracerHttp tracers))
            (myDbApplication (tracerDb  tracers))
```

