TITLE: Defining Application Tracers in Haskell
DESCRIPTION: Defines a record `Tracers` to hold tracers for different components like HTTP and DB. It uses higher-kinded types to represent different tracer configurations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emurgo/ogmios/blob/master/server/modules/contra-tracers/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: haskell
CODE:
```
data Tracers m (kind :: TracerDefinition) = Tracers
    { tracerHttp :: TracerHKD kind (Tracer m HttpLog)
    , tracerDb   :: TracerHKD kind (Tracer m DbLog)
    } deriving stock (Generic)
```

